1
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:58,960
What are you doing?

2
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:03,140
What's wrong with you?

3
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:05,319
Ren Zhen.

4
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:10,780
Brother Secretary! Brother Secretary!

5
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,200
Brother Secretary!

6
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,480
Nazahei, let's fly together.

7
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:18,160
Fly higher.

8
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:24,240
I want to fly higher.

9
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:28,600
Slow down.

10
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:29,800
It's fine. Slow down.

11
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,720
Grandpa Bate.

12
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,340
Let me play for a while.

13
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,640
This is a good thing my grandpa left for me.

14
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:38,560
Let me play for a while, Brother Secretary.

15
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,240
It'll break.

16
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,200
Jiao Li.

17
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:41,920
He drank too much.

18
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,280
Mr. Yin.

19
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,600
I'm fine.

20
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,120
I'm fine. Don't move.

21
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:53,520
Going home.

22
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:55,880
Slow down.

23
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,600
The fields and gardens are going to weed. Why not return?

24
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,000
Since I have made my heart a slave to my body,

25
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:08,440
why should I be melancholy and sorrowful alone?

26
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,240
Realize.

27
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,680
No, Wulan.

28
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,000
How much did he drink?

29
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,600
He drank too much.

30
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,720
This wine has no taste.

31
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:18,980
He drank it all at once.

32
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,120
It's not far.

33
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:20,930
Uncle Tuoka,

34
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,280
how strong is your wine?

35
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,680
It's over sixty degrees.

36
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:24,560
There's nothing wrong with this wine.

37
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,400
What's wrong?

38
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,890
Secretary, what's wrong with you?

39
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,600
Mr. Yin,

40
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,880
if it weren't for you,

41
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:36,079
I wouldn't even understand the meaning of this classical Chinese.

42
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,240
Secretary,

43
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,290
what's wrong with you, Secretary?

44
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:40,360
Aunt Guli,

45
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,440
why did you push her?

46
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,320
Why did you push her?

47
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,400
Oh, my secretary,

48
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,760
you still remember this.

49
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,000
Of course I remember.

50
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,320
What if she got hurt?

51
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,440
Apologize.

52
00:02:58,760 --> 00:02:59,240
Okay.

53
00:02:59,240 --> 00:02:59,880
It's fine.

54
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,240
I'm sorry, girl.

55
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,980
Don't do this, Secretary.

56
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:03,930
Are you okay?

57
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,610
It's fine. I'm okay.

58
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:09,960
Brother Secretary!

59
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,520
Brother Secretary!

60
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,480
Hold him.

61
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:13,900
Brother Secretary! Brother Secretary!

62
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,700
Brother Secretary, I'm fine.

63
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,440
Xiacun,

64
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,200
let's work hard together.

65
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,520
We will always be together.

66
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,640
Okay.

67
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,280
Secretary.

68
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:40,680
Wulan,

69
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,210
pour me a glass of water.

70
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,560
Thank you.

71
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,330
Why are you looking at me like that?

72
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,410
Brother Secretary.

73
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,180
It's best if you forget it all.

74
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,160
Why be melancholy

75
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,320
and grieve alone?

76
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,400
We must always stay together.

77
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,160
Jiao Li.

78
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,640
Alright, alright. Alright, alright.

79
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,520
Okay, okay.

80
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,700
Secretary.

81
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,280
I couldn't carry you.

82
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,340
Sister Ren Zhen carried you back.

83
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,080
Ren Zhen carried me back?

84
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,880
I didn't know

85
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,720
she was so strong.

86
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,680
She kindly carried you back,

87
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,900
but you still wouldn't let her go.

88
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,640
These are all my

89
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,090
certificates of honor.

90
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,440
Another one.

91
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,980
Graduation certificate.

92
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,780
Certificate of honor.

93
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,010
These are just like growing goji berries.

94
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:05,720
You reap what you sow.

95
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:08,040
I want Xia Village to win awards too.

96
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,800
The Most Beautiful Village,

97
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,320
Advanced Village, and Well-off Village.

98
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,520
Ren Zhen,

99
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,240
stand up.

100
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,640
Are you willing to

101
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,680
receive the award with me?

102
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,160
Help!

103
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,560
Oh, my god!

104
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,600
I know

105
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,840
you need time to accept yourself,

106
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,600
but you don't have much time left.

107
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,520
Sister Renzhen just sent a message

108
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,520
telling us to go to the cooperative.

109
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,159
Stop laughing.

110
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,480
Secretary,

111
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,240
going to the village committee?

112
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,000
Secretary,

113
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:53,640
no one is laughing at you.

114
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,520
Jiaoli, come and take a look.

115
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,960
Over half of the returns are fresh fruits,

116
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:14,880
which have the highest unit price

117
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,400
and the highest logistics cost.

118
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,200
I've looked at the pictures sent by this buyer.

119
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:18,640
Look.

120
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,720
They are severely damaged.

121
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,760
Some of them were already moldy

122
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,040
when they arrived.

123
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:28,960
For the ones piled up here,

124
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,420
I did a rough calculation.

125
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:32,450
The scrap rate is about 80 percent.

126
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,400
No.

127
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,520
The packaging must be outsourced.

128
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,850
Xiacun can't handle it.

129
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:37,680
It's my fault.

130
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,520
I knew we would gradually receive

131
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:43,010
some feedback from buyers these few days,

132
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,159
but I still let

133
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,400
the cooperative staff

134
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,800
go home for the holidays.

135
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,770
For the current situation,

136
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,380
I am sorry to everyone.

137
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,360
It's not about

138
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,020
who's sorry to whom right now.

139
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,120
The packaging issue must be solved as soon as possible.

140
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,720
I said it from the beginning.

141
00:06:58,840 --> 00:06:59,720
We should leave these things

142
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,080
to the professionals.

143
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,760
When it comes to packaging and transporting fresh fruit,

144
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,490
we can't afford to be careless.

145
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,760
How to pack it to avoid rolling around,

146
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,920
how to prevent it from getting crushed,

147
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,980
there's a set of rules for all of this.

148
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,450
I understand what you mean.

149
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,220
But I'm not planning to

150
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,140
outsource the packaging yet.

151
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:20,040
Do you still not understand the situation?

152
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:22,360
We worked so hard to build up the livestream.

153
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,440
Are we going to let it be ruined over this?

154
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,640
Don't worry just yet.

155
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,210
Everything takes time.

156
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,480
I'll handle this.

157
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,680
Outsourcing the packaging isn't

158
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,480
the only solution, right?

159
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,040
Yes.

160
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:37,240
The people of Xia Village know how to grow goji berries, I admit that.

161
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,280
But they don't know

162
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,640
how to deliver these fresh fruits

163
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:41,640
to customers thousands of miles away.

164
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:42,920
That's also a fact.

165
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,370
You have to admit it.

166
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,880
Have you ever thought about it?

167
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,520
These goji berries belong to the farmers.

168
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,120
They want to be involved too.

169
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,400
Ren Zhen, Party Secretary,

170
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,159
please don't argue.

171
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,200
See for yourself.

172
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:01,160
Party Secretary, you sent me rotten fruit.

173
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,160
My goji berries are rotten too.

174
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,960
The handsome guy is totally corrupted.

175
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,240
It's such a turn-off.

176
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,160
I supported rural revitalization,

177
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,620
and this is how you fool me.

178
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,970
Refund, stop dawdling.

179
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:13,200
Do you know

180
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,720
how hard it is to build customer trust?

181
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,280
If we mess up the first time,

182
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,960
it won't be that easy to get a second chance.

183
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:29,920
Mr. Liu.

184
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,120
Party Secretary,

185
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,720
your return rate is too high.

186
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:33,520
With all the back-and-forth,

187
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,520
we can't even cover our labor costs.

188
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:36,840
Whenever it's convenient,

189
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,240
please settle the payment.

190
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:38,970
Don't worry.

191
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:40,620
I won't default on my debt.

192
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,159
I just did the math.

193
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,840
With returns and refunds,

194
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,320
the loss could be a hundred thousand.

195
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,520
Plus the money we have to pay the courier

196
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,040
and the cost of the goji berries themselves,

197
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,080
not only will our livestream profits be wiped out,

198
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,760
but we'll also have to chip in another twenty thousand.

199
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,400
I'll cover the twenty thousand.

200
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,000
Wulan.

201
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,560
Don't let this get out.

202
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,320
They've worked hard for so long.

203
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,380
We can't let their efforts be in vain.

204
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,920
About the packaging problem,

205
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,320
you're not going to correct it at all, right?

206
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,040
Ren Zhen.

207
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,200
Aunt Guli and Uncle Tuoka,

208
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,880
volunteered to come and pack.

209
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,610
They didn't charge a penny.

210
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:17,640
I know

211
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,480
their packing techniques are unprofessional,

212
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,000
and their behavior is nonstandard.

213
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,130
But all of this can be

214
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,460
solved through professional training.

215
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,940
I know you advocate for outsourcing,

216
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,080
but I believe they can do it.

217
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,360
You invited me to Xia Village.

218
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,560
Now that I'm telling you

219
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,640
the most efficient way to work,

220
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,120
you refuse to listen.

221
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,760
Secretary.

222
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,480
I never let emotions

223
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,160
get in the way of my work.

224
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,240
But if you are so opinionated,

225
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,940
what am I still doing here?

226
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,050
Give it to me.

227
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,200
Sister Ren Zhen.

228
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,240
But efficiency

229
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,570
doesn't mean correctness.

230
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,520
Brother Secretary.

231
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,040
It's fine.

232
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,580
I can handle it.

233
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,920
I'll make some food and bring it to her.

234
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,580
And apologize while I'm at it.

235
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,020
She must be hungry too.

236
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,080
Secretary.

237
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,360
Ren Zhen...

238
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,640
Ren Zhen has left.
